    "AutonomyIn medical ethics, autonomy refers to ability for everyone to have a right to decide for themselves about their own treatment.",
    "Autonomy in relation to AI becomes more complex, as we willingly give over forms of control over decision-making power to machines [59].",
    "Autonomy means balancing what we decide to do for ourselves, and what we give over or delegate to systems and machines [59].",
    "It can refer to the ability for human agents to be able to choose when to implement, or what decisions to take based on AI recommendations.There is a crossover here with ethics in cyber security, as autonomy requires the ability for individuals to have access to their data and systems [14].",
